Name: Warung Barokah
Review Text: Delicious Halal Soul & Street Food from Indonesia, brought to you by Sri. We tried her Mie Bakso Soup with chewy beefballs and aromatic broth, and a plate of Tahu Ketoprak (my favorite 'less is more' streetfood) with tofu, soybean sprouts, peanut sauce and krupuk.

Name: Warung Barokah
Review Text: Great food, friendly staf, nice ambience, perfect for Indonesian dishes! Definitely will go back again!

Name: Warung Barokah
Review Text: Excellent service & yummy foods!! Mostly all foods at Warung Barokah are tasty, esp this rujak cingur! The ambience brought us to homeland Indonesia, the owner tante Sri along with the staffs are so friendly!

Name: Warung Barokah
Review Text: Authentic food, ketoprak and bakso beranak tasted just like in home country. Friendly ladies at the counter.

Name: Warung Barokah
Review Text: If you are craving for some Indonesian (javanese) dish that are more than famous nasi goreng or sate, then Warung Barokah would be a great choice. This is the real warung, no joking. There is Ibu Sri as the chef and owner, with her strong ‚Ä¶

Name: Warung Barokah
Review Text: I love how thematic and specialized Indo food in NL is. This one specializes in East Java food. All of the dishes I tried were flavorful, can be really spicy if you asked - hence i went here everyday during my stay in Ams. Different peanut ‚Ä¶

Name: Warung Barokah
Review Text: Hidden gem for foodies in Amsterdam. The price is surprisingly very affordable. The different between most of Indonesian restaurants in Amsterdam, this restaurant offer you a food stall instead of rice table with side dishes. Thus, you can choose your rice / noodle and side dishes that you like instead of having them all on the table.

Name: Warung Barokah
Review Text: Super authentic and hospitable owner/staff. My father is from East Java where Rujak Cingur is originated from and growing up I'd eat Rujak Cingur for afternoon snacks. Boy oh boy, this place reminds me of the local vendors back in Java! ‚Ä¶

Name: Warung Barokah

Name: Warung Barokah
Review Text: Recommended place to go when you are far away from home and miss comfort food. We tried bakso soup and nasi rames, they were really nice. The snacks were also very yummy.
